<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.212669>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. — Bunodosoma granuliferum. (A) Live specimen, lateral view. (B) Oral view. (C) Pedal disc view. (D) Lateral view. (E) Cross section through distal column. (F) Longitudinal section through column margin. (G – Q) Cnidae. — tentacles: (G) basitrich, (H) spirocyst; actinopharynx: (I) basitrich, (J) basitrich, (K) microbasic p - mastigophore; column: (L) basitrich, (M) basitrich; acrorhagi: (N) basitrich, (O) holotrich; filament: (P) basitrich, (Q) microbasic p - mastigophore. Abbreviations. — acr: acrorhagi, c: column, fo: fossa, msp: marginal sphincter, od: oral disc, pb: parietobasilar muscles, pd: pedal disc, rm: retractor muscles, s: siphonoglyph, t: tentacle, ve: vesicle. Scale bars. — A – D: 10 mm; E – F: 200 µm; G – Q: 25 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/212669/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

